metadata.name: Wires #183
metadata.description:
Cut, pulled, twisted wires.
Some reach their destination, others will never arrive.
Wires forming weaves and figures, sometimes linear, sometimes chaotic but, in their simplicity they create harmonious intertwining.

Press "p" to pause, press again "p" to start again.
Press "s" to save as jpg.

Generative artwork by Gandhiavelli, @gandhiavelli. Made with p5js in 2022.
License: CC BY-NC-ND 4.0

metadata.name: generator6 #140
metadata.description:
To eliminate any confusion, this is essentially identical to my previous mint except for one small change to the color and this kaleidoscope effect. This piece is celebrating 1000 followers on Twitter, as well as the new people who have recently picked up my work here.

The previous iteration in the "generator" series can be found here:

https://objkt.com/asset/hicetnunc/366931

This was previously a series I mostly used for giveaways or fun experimentation.

I have spent a significant amount of time at raves in fields, just putting that out there.

metadata.name: Pines #85
metadata.description:
A combination of pine trees, hills and mountains put together in a way that represents nature in it's true form.

Everything is generated by code by drawing pixels on a canvas using Javascript.
The simplex-noise library was used to generate the hills and the mountains.

I hope you like this piece!

metadata.name: Dos Carratas Jr #40
metadata.description:
Notorious Lucha libre, BWE wrestler, and fan favourite, Dos Carratas Jr is an absolute gentleman outside of the ring. And a terror when he climbs inside. But one thing stays the same, whether he's inside the ring, or outside, as a strict rule, the mask always stays on. Even his baby bunnies have no idea what pappa looks like. 

'r' toggles auto-rotate. ‘l’ toggles mouse following

“What’s a bunny’s favourite music?”
“What do you call a rabbit comedian?”
“What is orange and sounds like a parrot?”
“How can you say rabbit without using the letter R?”

metadata.name: Mark One: Atoms of Space #34
metadata.description:
This piece is dedicated to the 50+ years old industrial plants. Like nuclear power stations where they still use pre DOS era hardware and software.

So using the original DOS font is quite a modern approach - it just depends on the context.

metadata.name: Caught in a Void #255

p5.js

metadata.name: Planet Panels #60
metadata.description:
Stylised isometric terrain with a shifting hand-drawn aesthetic.

Fully deterministic but the higher your viewport the more terrain will be drawn, this is preferable to fixed scaling.

metadata.name: Grud #5
metadata.description:
Grud, a speedrun on 31st May 2022. 

The cousin of the BoodMoards, exploring some other shapes, colours and fun ideas. 

Made with p5js. 
23 colour palettes
10 background colours 
11 tile styles 

Big thanks to all collectors and shoutout to the Circolors frens for the support <3 

10% of mint proceeds going to the processing foundation 
42% of royalties to minters. 

Click the image or press 's' or 'S' in live mode to save a 2160 × 2700 png
